The Tokyo Regional Taxation Bureau hasimposed a penalty tax on &lt;Fuji Bank Ltd> for alleged improperuse of tax-free reserves, a bank spokeswoman told Reuters.    She declined to reveal the bank's planned response butanother bank official said it has not paid the penalty.    The bank said in a brief statement it believes that its useof the tax-free reserves is legal.    Financial institutions can set aside 0.003 pct of theirrisky loans as tax-free reserves. Fuji said a difference ofunderstanding exists between the bank and the tax bureauregarding the use of tax-free reserves. It did not elaborate.    Fuji Bank reported a 72.1 billion yen net profit in the1985/86 year. Lending totaled 16,120 billion yen. REUTER&#3;